helpdesk-note.body:
Spencer,
I'd be interested in hearing what rumors are going around! It might bring a little levity into our long nights.
I absolutely appreciate your frustration during these problems. I can tell you that most of us are equally frustrated, and exhausted. I know the communications you and the faculty and staff are getting are vague. We are doing everything we can, and some of us have been putting in very long hours, sacrificing sleep, and meals, and even family.
We are working on alternatives to provide services - such as printing - in a way that doesn't rely on other services. As you may be aware, there are a large number of interdependant services, and anything we change now will need to be changed back once the issues have been contained. We have a small but dedicated staff, and we ask that you bear with us while we do everything we can to offer you the services you expect.
I'm sure this isn't as informative as you'd hoped, and for that I apologize.
Thanks,
Paul Fabian MSOE Director of IT Services fabian@msoe.edu (414) 277-2355

helpdesk-ticket.subject: MSOE Library Proxy Server
helpdesk-ticket.description: Hello Support, I don't know what the status of the situation is with respect to the IT hardware repairs this morning. However, this morning, the library proxy server appears to continue to not be functioning. Because the proxy server is down, access to the library databases also does not work via the library website. The proxy server URL is built into the database links so that remote access users can authenticate in order to access the databases. We are working on setting up a databases page that features direct links to the databases, so that at least users on campus can access the databases. My questions are: [1] Would someone in IT please provide me with a status update as to when we can expect the proxy server to be functioning again? [2] Assuming that hardware repairs are completed, would IT personnel please verify that the proxy server is re-started and is up and running? Thanks, Gary Shimek Director of the Library
helpdesk-ticket.description-html:
Hello Support,

I don't know what the status of the situation is with respect to the IT hardware repairs this morning.  However, this morning, the library proxy server appears to continue to not be functioning.  Because the proxy server is down, access to the library databases also does not work via the library website.  The proxy server URL is built into the database links so that remote access users can authenticate in order to access the databases.  We are working on setting up a databases page that features direct links to the databases, so that at least users on campus can access the databases.

My questions are:

[1]  Would someone in IT please provide me with a status update as to when we can expect the proxy server to be functioning again?

[2]  Assuming that hardware repairs are completed, would IT personnel please verify that the proxy server is re-started and is up and running?

Thanks,

Gary Shimek
Director of the Library

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Constant Lockouts
helpdesk-ticket.description:
Hello,
My name is Thomas Hartwick, and I am having continuous issues with my MSOE Id/Password. My password expired in the middle of the server outage, and I had is reset. This worked when I was on campus, but I couldn't log in as soon as I left campus. I also could not log back in when I returned to campus. I erased all the stored passwords on my phone and computer because IT said that may be contributing to the issue.
Now it seems as though I am constantly locked out, and IT is getting invalid password attempts when I myself am not trying to log into anything. This has resulted in my computer being constantly locked out and my inability to do schoolwork the past 2 weeks.
I hope this helps diagnose the problem.
Sincerely, Thomas Hartwick.

helpdesk-ticket.subject: CBM Website Down at Crucial Time!
helpdesk-ticket.description:
Morning Helpdesk and Mike,
I was doing some work this morning and suddenly noticed that the Center for BioMolecular Modeling website (http://cbm.msoe.edu) is completely down - at least anywhere I have been able to try it.
This is a crucial problem for today/Sunday, as we have several national events running across the country involving hundreds of students that will be using this website for their competitions (specifically the science olympiad pages at http://cbm.msoe.edu/scienceOlympiad).
To my understanding, the site was going to remain live during the IT work this week, since any CBM databases were removed/disconnected. If that was not going to be the case, I could have arranged to have it hosted elsewhere (like my personal webspace), even if just temporarily. But at this point, all of these competition events expect to visit the links provided for our CBM site.
What can we do about this? Is there anyone else I can contact to help resolve this?
- Mark
PS: Also, I was originally going to email about an another issue, but this is far less urgent than the CBM site. Basically, yesterday afternoon we received a plethora of blank submissions to some of our summer workshop application forms (http://cbm.msoe.edu/teacherWorkshops/). They all came from within about an hour, and there must have been literally hundreds of them. . . many listing the sender's email address as "/foo@cbmprod.msoe.edu". Could this be related to the continued IT work? Is it maybe a separate issue like a spamming attack? Any thoughts would be appreciated - I have CC'd one of the blank submissions below.
MSOE Center for BioMolecular Modeling - http://cbm.msoe.edu 3D Molecular Designs - www.3dmoleculardesigns.com hoelzer@msoe.edu office: 414-277-4554 cell: 414-640-8668

helpdesk-note.body:
Thanks Chris - you saved the day! From what I've heard, all of the weekend events went off without much trouble. . . and looking forward, I don't think we have any other events until after the holiday break, so hopefully things will be back up and running in full by then.
As for your comment about the emails being disabled, is that in regards to the course forms below, each of which sends the submission to us in an email?
http://cbm.msoe.edu/teacherWorkshops/mmwApplication.php
http://cbm.msoe.edu/teacherWorkshops/ggpmApplication.php
http://cbm.msoe.edu/teacherWorkshops/ddtyApplication.php
http://cbm.msoe.edu/teacherWorkshops/3dApplication.php
If so, we would like those to be active as soon as possible, as we have teachers applying to our courses regularly. If we continue to have trouble with blank submissions (we've gotten a few blank ones here and there, but nothing ever like the massive hundreds that came in over a matter of minutes last week!), we would like to have the same CAPTCHA added to these forms as you had added to our Science Olympiad online form.
Speaking of S.O. stuff, any idea what the timeline would be for having that data-base driven form live again? I've been making due by getting the information through emails, but it would be great to have it automated again.
I'd be happy to chat with you in person about any of this if I didn't describe anything clearly - and thanks as always.
-Mark

helpdesk-note.body:
Good morning Chris, Mike and IT helpdesk team,
Last week we had a number of blank (I assume spamming) submissions arrive from our online course applications (see URLs below to visit these application pages). We always get a few blank ones here and there, but nothing like the massive hundreds that came in over a matter of minutes last week!
http://cbm.msoe.edu/teacherWorkshops/mmwApplication.php
http://cbm.msoe.edu/teacherWorkshops/ggpmApplication.php
http://cbm.msoe.edu/teacherWorkshops/ddtyApplication.php
http://cbm.msoe.edu/teacherWorkshops/3dApplication.php
Based on Chris' email from December 12 (below) and the few submission tests I had time to do this morning, it looks like the ability for these forms to submit emails has been completely dis-activated. We would like those to be active as soon as possible, as we have teachers applying to our courses regularly - and especially over the holiday break.
If we continue to have significant trouble with blank submissions, we would like to have the same CAPTCHA added to these forms as you had added to our Science Olympiad online form. . . but I think we need to at least turn the email capabilities back on for now and see what happens, since we may be loosing submissions every day.
Please let me know as soon as this has been done so I can re-post the forms and make them live again.
- Mark

Hi Jack,
I just called and left you a message regarding your options for disabling email forwarding. Since we are experiencing a partial systems outage, you currently have 2 options available to you to disable the email forwarding:
1. Come in to the MSOE IT helpdesk and we can reset your password after verifying your ID in person and walk you through the steps to disable the forwarding. If you have your MSOE laptop it would be helpful, but not necessary.
2. We are expecting the sever outage to end by the start of this coming week. When the system is fully restored you can go to pwd.msoe.edu to rest your password and then use these instructions to disable your email forwarding: https://support.office.com/en-au/article/Forward-email-to-another-email-account-1ed4ee1e-74f8-4f53-a174-86b748ff6a0e
I hope these options help.
Please let me know how you'd like to procede,
Michael

The account will expire 2 years after your date of graduation. helpdesk-ticket.subject: Can't see H Drive
helpdesk-ticket.description: Since server outage, Susan has been unable to see the H drive.
helpdesk-ticket.description-html: Since server outage, Susan has been unable to see the H drive.

helpdesk-note.body:
Two things you can try.
First go to Start, search for "Command Prompt", right click on it, select Run as Administrator. The command prompt should open.
Type gpupdate/force and hit enter. Some stuff should show up in the box and you will be prompted to reboot. Restart and you should then be able to see the H drive again.
Other thing you can try:
Go to Start>Computer>Map Network Drive. Set the drive to H and for file enter: \\homestore\homedrives$\becker and click finish.
You may have to restart the computer for it to update.
Please let me know if you are able to access it or not! Abby Griffin Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/3742

From: fimservice@msoe.edu [mailto:fimservice@msoe.edu] Sent: Tuesday, December 15, 2015 1:01 AM To: Moskalik, Dr. Katrina Subject: Your MSOE account password is going to expire soon!
Your MSOE account password is scheduled to expire on 12/17/2015.
[MSOE Logo][Milwaukee School of Engineering]<http://www.msoe.edu>
Hello Katrina,
The password for your MSOE account (moskalik@msoe.edu<mailto:moskalik@msoe.edu>) is scheduled to expire on 12/17/2015. It is highly recommended to change the password for this account prior to 12/17/2015 to avoid any disruption in access. If you do not change the password before the expiration date, access to MSOE systems will be disabled.
Log on to the MSOE password reset portal at pwd.msoe.edu<https://pwd.msoe.edu> and reset your password using the security questions previously provided.
If you have not yet registered for the MSOE password reset portal, go to pwdreg.msoe.edu<https://pwdreg.msoe.edu> and complete the registration process prior to changing your password.
Your new password must meet the following criteria:

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Projector in L304 not shutting down properly
helpdesk-ticket.description:
WHen I walked into class this afternoon, the projector doors were open on the projectors, indicating the projection system was on. However, the crestron was in its default "start system" operational mode. I turned the system on and things worked normally. However, at the end of my lecture when I went to shutdown the system, the crestron showed that the system was shutting down while the projectors continued to show a no input image. After 2 minutes, the crestron display showed a start system display. However, the projectors still had their doors opened and the bulbs were still dimly turned on.
I will be leaving the room shortly, but this may be a higher priority fix, if only to prevent the bulb from burning overnight if no one is in this room after me.

helpdesk-ticket.description: Batteries for CC 49 card reader are dead, and need to be replaced.
helpdesk-ticket.description-html: Batteries for CC 49 card reader are dead, and need to be replaced.

helpdesk-note.body: sending to hardware team
helpdesk-note.body-html: sending to hardware team

helpdesk-note.body: I will go and replace them soon, will update when done.
helpdesk-note.body-html: I will go and replace them soon, will update when done.

helpdesk-note.body:
Just a heads up,
The battery packs that fit in the doors are getting old and as the batteries corrode over time in the packs it is ruining the metal connectors. I couldn't find any replacement packs in B closet with the rest of the shlage equipment so I just cleaned the corroded connectors with a wire brush and razor blade. Works perfectly now.
TL;DR When replacing batteries, check and clean connectors before putting in new batteries.
helpdesk-note.body-html:
Just a heads up, 

The battery packs that fit in the doors are getting old and as the batteries corrode over time in the packs it is ruining the metal connectors. I couldn't find any replacement packs in B closet with the rest of the shlage equipment so I just cleaned the corroded connectors with a wire brush and razor blade. Works perfectly now. 

TL;DR
When replacing batteries, check and clean connectors before putting in new batteries.

helpdesk-ticket.subject: No Creation of Alumni-Address possible
helpdesk-ticket.description:
Hello Ladies and Gentlemen,
I already asked Jennifer Laur regarding an occurring problem and would like to forward this email to you.
"Hey Jen,
thank you for letting me know! I am really excited to get the diploma ;)
But I have one more question for you: Do you know why the german students aren’t able to create an alumni-address? When filling out the application for the mail address, we get the following message:
"Your request for an account needs to be processed further. Please ensure you are inputting your information correctly. Common mistakes include: using non-legal first name, not using your earliest graduation year, and using a birthdate not in the format mmddyyyy. We will email you again once the account is ready for use.“
I got this error message twice ( one before my official graduation date and the second one a week ago ) and I never got any other email regarding this issue. I mean, it would be nice for us to get this alumni-address to never forget MSOE and stay in touch with Milwaukee ;)
Please let me know, if you know something :)
Best wishes from Germany,
Jörn“
Can you maybe help me? I also got an email saying that my account is scheduled to expire on 12/30/2015. and i would like to keep in touch with the MSOE!
Please let me know, if you can help me!
Best regards from Germany,
Jörn

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Account Unlocked
helpdesk-ticket.description: Rebecca Ploeckelman from HR called, unable to connect to email in outlook client and outlook.com/msoe.edu. I noticed in Lockout Status that there were some bad attempts at ~7:27am and her account was locked out. She mentioned that she had tried to log onto outlook.com and it had rejected her, saying bad credentials. I unlocked her account, she was able to log into her mail account online and in the client. So far, no more bad attempts so no follow up is needed. This ticket is for our records.

helpdesk-ticket.subject: FW: Your MSOE account password is going to expire soon!
helpdesk-ticket.description:
I reset my password on Monday and I am sitting receiving these emails. Is there something more I need to do?
Thanks, Dana Grennier grennier@msoe.edu
From: fimservice@msoe.edu [mailto:fimservice@msoe.edu] Sent: Thursday, December 17, 2015 1:00 AM To: Grennier, Dana-Marie Subject: Your MSOE account password is going to expire soon!
Your MSOE account password is scheduled to expire on 12/20/2015.
[MSOE Logo][Milwaukee School of Engineering]<http://www.msoe.edu>
Hello Dana-Marie,
The password for your MSOE account (grennier@msoe.edu<mailto:grennier@msoe.edu>) is scheduled to expire on 12/20/2015. It is highly recommended to change the password for this account prior to 12/20/2015 to avoid any disruption in access. If you do not change the password before the expiration date, access to MSOE systems will be disabled.
Log on to the MSOE password reset portal at pwd.msoe.edu<https://pwd.msoe.edu> and reset your password using the security questions previously provided.
If you have not yet registered for the MSOE password reset portal, go to pwdreg.msoe.edu<https://pwdreg.msoe.edu> and complete the registration process prior to changing your password.
Your new password must meet the following criteria:
* Passwords must be at least 8 characters * Passwords must include at least 3 out of these 4 items: * Uppercase letter * Lowercase letter * A number * A symbol Note: The previous four passwords are remembered by the system, so you will need to use a unique password each time your password changes.
Please contact the Help Desk<http://helpdesk.msoe.edu> if you have any questions or problems resetting your password.
No MSOE employees nor any MSOE correspondence will ever ask you for your account password.​
Thank you, The MSOE Help Desk (414) 277-7288
This email was sent by an automated process.
Milwaukee School of Engineering 1025 North Broadway • Milwaukee, WI 53202-3109 (800) 332-6763 / explore@msoe.edu<mailto:explore@msoe.edu>

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Walt,
I think that we are seeing issues because the projectors are not being turned off. What I'm seeing in several rooms is that if an instructor logs off, but doesn't shut down, the entire system goes into a sleep mode instead of shutting down properly. I've spent some time in L304 re-setting everything back, and it appears to be working. I've also reached out to the instructors that were still "on" the system, and asked that they help us by completely logging off when they are done with the desktop computer. The next instructor can then login, and it should work better. It all seems to be working properly right now, except for the VGA cable (which I plan to have a student replace when they return). I will continue to watch this issue in several of the rooms in the L-300 wing, and hopefully we can prevent some future issues. Thanks for the heads up on this. Pat Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/3852

helpdesk-note.body-html:
Hi Walt,

I think that we are seeing issues because the projectors are not being turned off. What I'm seeing in several rooms is that if an instructor logs off, but doesn't shut down, the entire system goes into a sleep mode instead of shutting down properly.  I've spent some time in L304 re-setting everything back, and it appears to be working. I've also reached out to the instructors that were still "on" the system, and asked that they help us by completely logging off when they are done with the desktop computer. The next instructor can then login, and it should work better. It all seems to be working properly right now, except for the VGA cable (which I plan to have a student replace when they return).
I will continue to watch this issue in several of the rooms in the L-300 wing, and hopefully we can prevent some future issues.
Thanks for the heads up on this.
Pat

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Jason, Even a regular piece of paper will not scan. I have personally tried this myself, and just watched someone yesterday try and fail to scan a document.
Here is the sequence of events: Login. Select scan from main menu, as opposed to copy or release. Select “Me” as email destination. Or entering an alternative email manually. Scan document(s). Press blue button to begin sending scanned data email. Wait. Receive error message saying, “Failed to complete the job. Please check the Job History. Job no: 3543” Looking at the Job History page, the job will say “Error Deletion”. Clicking on the details of the job will report the following.
Job No.: 3543 Result: Error Deletion Error Det.: Server Connection Error Username: ertelj File Name: SMLH_554e16012717030 Address: ertelj@msoe.edu<mailto:ertelj@msoe.edu> Date/time: New, 01/27/2016, 17:03, Type No of Originals: 1
Selecting External Server Info on the job details page will report, External Server Info Job No: 3543 Server Name: papercut
Thank you,
Jacob Ertel Milwaukee School of Engineering Cell: 262-490-5956

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Resetting Password
helpdesk-ticket.description:
Hello,
I have tried to reset my password (which is about to expire) but was not granted access to the system for some reason. I will try again later today, but usually have some kind of problem with this process.
If you could reset my current password before it expires on Monday, that would be very helpful. I have many emailed student papers to grade during the holiday break, so it would be very inconvenient to lose access to my account.
Thank you very much.
Elizabeth L. Clark
clark@msoe.edu
User Name: clark
